== 电子政务争论 ==
=== 劣势 ===
电子政务的主要劣势是公众缺乏对网络使用的平等性，网络信息可靠性、以及可能影响、偏差公众意见的隐藏政府机构。

设计、实施电子政务有很多潜在影响，包括政府和公民的[[非中介化|非中介化]]，对经济、社会、政治的影响因素、对[[黑客袭击|黑客袭击]]的脆弱性和对现状的干扰。<ref name="information137">{{Cite book | last1 = Atkinson | first1 = Robert D. | last2 = Castro | first2 = Daniel | title = Digital Quality of Life | publisher = The Information Technology and Innovation Foundation | pages = 137–145 | year = 2008 | url = http://www.itif.org/files/DQOL-14.pdf | format = PDF | access-date = 2012-09-19 | archive-date = 2012-03-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120306125039/http://www.itif.org/files/DQOL-14.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref> 参见[[电子巨兽|电子巨兽]]。

==== 高级监控 ====
政府和公民的过度接触是把双刃剑，一旦采取电子政务，并且系统越来越复杂，公民就必须在网上与政府沟通，范围越来越广。这就导致公民的隐私权受到威胁，政府可以获得越来越多的公民信息。在最坏情况下，政府和公民之间越来越多信息通过互联网传输，会发展为[[专制|专制]]系统。政府一旦希望，可以获得无数公民的个人信息，个人[[隐私|隐私]]将不复存在。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.technewsworld.com/story/48629.html?wlc=1235202183 |title=AT&T Sued for Role in Aiding US Government Surveillance |publisher=TechNewsWorld |author=Lyman, Jay |date=2006-02-01 |accessdate=2009-02-28 |archive-date=2011-06-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609112218/http://www.technewsworld.com/story/48629.html?wlc=1235202183 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.wired.com/27bstroke6/2007/08/analysis-new-la.html |title=Analysis: New Law Gives Government Six Months to Turn Internet and Phone Systems into Permanent Spying Architecture |publisher=[[Wired_(magazine)|Wired]] |author=Singel, Ryan |date=2007-08-06 |accessdate=2008-02-28 |archive-date=2008-03-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080313160545/http://blog.wired.com/27bstroke6/2007/08/analysis-new-la.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

