==== 民主化 ====
{{Main|电子民主化}}
电子政务的目标还包括公民参与，通过网络，全国人民可以与政治家、官员互动，倾听他们的声音。[[微博|微博]]和互动调查可以让政治家和公仆看到人民的主要诉求。[[聊天室|聊天室]]可以让公民实时接触到参选官员，看到他们的办公室，和官员直接交流，允许选民直观感受政府影响。这些科技可以让政府更透明，让选民更明白他们的税负如何使用。让选民更明白应该选谁，如何让官员更有生产效率。
理论上，政府可以利用电子政务实现自身的更加[[民主|民主]]。[[政府透明度|政府透明度]]可以让公众了解，政府如何做决策，让参选官员对其行为更加负责。公众可以更加直接、显著地影响政府的立法。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.usatoday.com/tech/columnist/ericjsinrod/2004-06-30-sinrod_x.htm |title=A look at the pros and cons of e-government |publisher=[[USA_Today|USA Today]] |author=Sinrod, Eric J. |date=2004-06-30 |accessdate=2008-03-01 |archive-date=2008-01-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080127024357/http://www.usatoday.com/tech/columnist/ericjsinrod/2004-06-30-sinrod_x.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.govtech.com/dc/articles/417520 |title=How Web 2.0 Will Transform Local Government |publisher=Digital Communities |author=Schrier, Bill |date=2008-10-17 |accessdate=2008-03-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081023020229/http://www.govtech.com/dc/articles/417520 |archivedate=2008-10-23 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdt.org/egov/handbook/transparency.shtml |title=Transparency |publisher=Center for Democracy & Technology |accessdate=2009-03-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090315105326/http://cdt.org/egov/handbook/transparency.shtml |archivedate=2009-03-15 }} </ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e.govt.nz/resources/research/progress/transformation/chapter13.html |title=Facilitating effective online participation in e-government |publisher=E-government in [[New_Zealand|New Zealand]] |author=Thorpe, Stephen |accessdate=2009-03-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081015040625/http://www.e.govt.nz/resources/research/progress/transformation/chapter13.html |archivedate=2008-10-15 }} </ref>

